            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Hd1e108">Rubrica 2</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De moralitate</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>
      ¶ De moralitate. Rubrica. 2.
      
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e119">
               <lb ed="#V" n="65"/> <ref>ARistoteles rethor.
      <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>lib. 2. c.
      <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>16.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Qd1e127">Iuuenes non sunt maligni mo
        <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>Lris: sed facilis moris: propierea quod non
        <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>dum viderunt multas nequitias.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e135">
               <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>
            ¶ <ref>Seneca de ira li. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Qd1e139">Sumuntur a conuersanti
        <lb ed="#V" n="71" break="no"/>bus mores. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e146"> /
       <ref>Idem de moribus.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Qd1e148">Educatio
        <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>et disciplina mores faciunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e154">
               <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>
            ¶ <ref>Lex diges. ti. de condi. insti. li. filius.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Qd1e158">Que conti bo
        <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>nos mores sunt nec facem nos posse credendum est </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e164">
               <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>
            ¶ <ref>Ualerius max. li. 6. ti.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Qd1e168">de mutatione morum
        <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>Lucius silla vsque ad questure sue comitia
        <lb ed="#V" n="77"/>vitam libidine vino ludicre artis amore inqui
        <lb ed="#V" n="78"/>natam perduxit. Quapropter. 6. marium consulem
        <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>moleste tulisse traditur quod sibi asperrimum in
        <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>affrica baellum gerenti tam delicatus questor sor
        <lb ed="#V" n="81"/>te obuenisset: eiusdem virtus quisi preruptis et
        <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>disiectis nequitie qua obscidebatur claustris
        <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>cathenas iugurte iniecit manibus mitrida
        <lb ed="#V" n="84" break="no"/>tem compescuit. Sociales belli luctus repres
        <lb ed="#V" n="85" break="no"/>sit: et hoc ne dominationem fregit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e193"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Qd1e195">Tenustodis <!--no reference -->
        <lb ed="#V" n="86"/>adolescentiam piget attingere: siue patrem aspi
        <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>ciam abdicationis iniungentem notam: si
        <lb ed="#V" n="88" break="no"/>ue matrem suspendio finire vitam propter
        <lb ed="#V" n="89"/>filii turpitudinem coactam: cum omnium <!--65.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="19-v"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>postea graii sanguinis virorum extiterit: me
        <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>diumque europe et asie vel spet vel despera.
        <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>tionis pignus fuerit: hic enim eum salutis
        <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>sue patronum habuit: illa vadem victorie
        <lb ed="#V" n="5"/>assumpsit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e225">
               <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>
            ¶ <ref>Cassiodorus epistolarum libro. 11. ca. 2.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="7"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Qd1e229">Raro omnium bortum est dominum trium
        <lb ed="#V" n="8" break="no"/>phare demoribus. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e237">
               <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>
            ¶ <ref>Isidorus soliloquiorum li. 2. c. 41.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Qd1e241">Assidui
        <lb ed="#V" n="10" break="no"/>tas mores facit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e248">
               <lb ed="#V" n="11"/>
               ¶ <ref>Bernardus li.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Qd1e252">de contemptu mundi: Colli
        <lb ed="#V" n="12" break="no"/>ge thesaurum: qui gemmas vincit et aurum.
        <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>Quere bonos mores thesauros interiores. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e260">
               <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>
            ¶ <ref>Ricardus iudex venusinus li. de pertracta
        <lb ed="#V" n="15"/>tione nuptur. c. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Qd1e264">Usus et mores: seris formam
        <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>tur ab annis. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e272">
               <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>
            ¶ <ref>Montenarius inluna cleri. c. 59.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Qd1e276">Qualis
        <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>conuictus talis formatio morum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-d1e282">
               <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>
            ¶ <ref>Prouerb.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d14180-Qd1e286">metricum exordinem. vel vagam.
        <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>Cum fueris rome: romano viuito more.
        <lb ed="#V" n="21"/>Cum sueris alibi: viuito sicut ibi. </quote>
            </p>
